      "HVAC shut off, dampers closed, electrical isolations in place",
      "Fire pumps activated",
      "Fire Team 2 deployed to extinguish fire",
      "Fire hoses used with solid water bursts",
      "Fire reflashed and was immediately extinguished",
      "All clear given at 16:54",
      "Linen closet sealed for investigation"
    ],
    "summary": "On December 13, 2015, a fire occurred in the B-Deck linen closet during drilling operations on the drill ship Maersk Valiant. The fire was caused by improper storage of combustible materials susceptible to spontaneous heating or chemical reaction. An offshore travel bag tested positive for organic oils, and an unsealed facial cream container was found in the closet. The fire was extinguished after 17 minutes using fire hoses. Estimated damage was $10,000. The incident resulted in a full crew muster and deployment of Fire Team 2.",
